@rlevas , @zeroflag , @dlysnichenko Thank you all for your comments; I incorporated them and added a new CLI option to support Trusted Proxy setup in non-interactive mode (see `--tproxy-configuration-file-path`). In addition to uni testing I executed some E2E tests - as usual - to make sure the tool works as expected with the following outcome: ``` $ ambari-server setup-trusted-proxy --ambari-admin-username=admin --ambari-admin-password=admin --tproxy-enabled=true --tproxy-configuration-file-path=my/path/tproxy.configs -v Using python /usr/bin/python Setting up Trusted Proxy support... INFO: Loading properties from /etc/ambari-server/conf/ambari.properties INFO: Setup Trusted Proxy INFO: about to run command: ps -p 19757 INFO: process_pid=15668 INFO: Loading properties from /etc/ambari-server/conf/ambari.properties INFO: Fetching Trusted Proxy configuration from DB INFO: Fetching information from Ambari's REST API Ambari Server 'setup-trusted-proxy' completed successfully. $ cat my/path/tproxy.configs [ { "proxyuser" : "knox", "hosts" : "host1", "users" : "user1", "groups" : "group1" }, { "proxyuser" : "admin", "hosts" : "host2", "users" : "user2, user3", "groups" : "group2" } ] $ambari-server setup-trusted-proxy --ambari-admin-username=admin --ambari-admin-password=admin --tproxy-enabled=true --tproxy-configuration-file-path=my/path/nonExisting.configs -v Using python /usr/bin/python Setting up Trusted Proxy support... INFO: Loading properties from /etc/ambari-server/conf/ambari.properties INFO: Setup Trusted Proxy INFO: about to run command: ps -p 19757 INFO: process_pid=16144 ERROR: Exiting with exit code 1. REASON: The following errors occurred while processing your request: ['--tproxy-configuration-file-path is set to a non-existing file: my/path/nonExisting.configs'] ```
